cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI

This paper proposes an algorithm for spatiotemporal MEs spotting, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and thresholding techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with emotional deception and high-stakes environments, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper uses a recurrent convolutional autoencoder for feature representation, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
